  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="MuTA40">
<l>uḷaṉkaṇṭāy naṉṉeñcē yuttama ṉeṉṟu</l>
<l>muḷaṉkaṇṭā yuḷḷuvā ruḷḷat – tuḷaṉkaṇṭāy</l>
<l>viṇṇoṭuṅkak kōṭuyarum vīṅkaruvi vēṅkaṭattāṉ</l>
<l>maṇṇoṭuṅkat tāṉaḷanta maṉ</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>He is, look, good heart. Ever the highest</l>
<l>is he, look. In the hearts of those who think [of him] is he, see,</l>
<l>the one from Vēṅkaṭam with swelling waterfalls where peaks are so high</l> 
<l>as to hide the sky, the king who secretly<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">The infinitive oṭuṅka may be understood here as an adverb, “secretly”, alluding to the fact that the dwarf in measuring the earth tricked Mahābali as he hid his real intention.</note> measured the earth.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
